```

Can't figure out for the life of me what I am doing wrong.  It's probably something simple I am overlooking. Any help would be appreciated!!

@josuedelgado123 I too tried CellIs with equal and it wound up applying the fill to all blank cells.

Looks like I'm quite late here.
Could not get cellIs to work, however achieved the same result using custom expression

```
worksheet.addConditionalFormatting({
      ref: 'A2:Z100',
      rules: [
        {
          type: 'expression',
          formulae: ['A2="T"'],
          style: {fill: {type: 'pattern', pattern: 'solid', bgColor: {argb: 'FF00FF00'}}}
        }
      ]
    });
```

Basically, Formulae based on cell values use the top-left addr as this gets translated

Ref: https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/2ab468b8bae2c8d5844f922d61ac7d960fee26be/TODO.txt
